{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.15","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The library has been completely updated for Swift 6 language mode, and now compiles in strict"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"concurrency with no warnings or errors."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.15"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The library is now 100% Swift 6 compatible, and has been done in a way that is full backwards","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"compatible. If your project does not have strict concurrency warnings turned on, then updating","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the Composable Architecture to 1.15.0 should not cause any compilation errors. However, if you have","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"strict concurrency turned on, then you may come across a few situations you need to update.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Enum cases as function references","type":"heading","anchor":"Enum-cases-as-function-references","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is common to use the case of enum as a function, such as mapping on an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Effect"},{"type":"text","text":" to bundle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"its output into an action:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["return client.fetch()","  .map(Action.response)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In strict concurrency mode this may fail with a message like this:","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"🛑 Converting non-sendable function value to ‘@Sendable (Value) -> Action’ may introduce data races","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are two ways to fix this. You can either open the closure explicitly instead of using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"Action.response","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" as a function:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["return client.fetch()","  .map { .response($0) }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is also an upcoming Swift feature that will fix this. You can enable it in an SPM package"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by adding a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enableUpcomingFeature"},{"type":"text","text":" to its Swift settings:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["swiftSettings: [","  .enableUpcomingFeature(\"InferSendableFromCaptures\"),","]),"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"And you can ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/www.swift.org\/blog\/using-upcoming-feature-flags\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"by navigating to your project’s build settings in Xcode, and adding a new “Other Swift Flags” flag:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["-enable-upcoming-feature InferSendableFromCaptures"]}]}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"title":"Migrating to 1.15","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.19","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitect